added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Punos Fuertes
added.description: Harto de perder cuando juega a los videojuegos contra su padre, Craig busca entrenarse en el Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Three Girls and a Monster/Monkey See, Doggy Two
added.description: Three Girls and a Monster: The girls are once again in a furious battle with a ferocious monster. But Blossom and Buttercup can't agree on how to fight the beast and Bubbles just wants everyone to get along./Monkey See, Doggy Two: Mojo has discovered a fatal flaw in his brilliant plan and decides to reenact it step-by-step. The girls think they're experiencing deja vu but it's really just Mojo working his maniacal mischief.

added.title: Jewel of the Aisle/Super Zeroes
added.description: Jewel of the Isle: A crook hides a huge diamond in a box of the girls' favorite cereal. But how can he trick the girls into giving him some cereal in order to get the jewel back?/Super Zeroes: The girls don't think they have enough superhero accessories like those found in the comic books. They begin to emulate their favorite characters, complete with gadgets and gizmos.

added.title: Candy Is Dandy/Catastrophe
added.description: Candy Is Dandy: When the Mayor gives the girls some candy in gratitude for saving the day, they become hooked on the stuff. They even make a deal with a local villain to commit crimes for treats./Catastrophe: A monster is frantically tearing up the town looking for his lost kitty. But in a city the size of Townsville, how can the girls find one lone cat?

added.title: Gettin' Twiggy with It/Cop Out
added.description: Getting' Twiggy with It: Mitch takes Twiggy, the class hamster, home for the weekend. But when Mitch flushes Twiggy down the toilet, he emerges bigger and badder than ever./Cop Out: A lazy Townsville cop gets fired and blames the girls for saving the day too often, thereby stealing his job. Now, it's payback time and he has the perfect plan to stop those pint-size punks.

added.title: Hot Air Buffoon/Ploys R' Us
added.description: Hot Air Buffoon: The Mayor realizes the girls are doing all the work in his city for him. So he mans a hot air balloon and starts fighting crime the old-fashioned way./Ploys R' Us: The girls wake up to find their room filled with toys. They soon figure out that the Professor has been sleepwalking and stealing. Instead of reporting it, the girls take advantage of the situation.

added.title: Bibi's Do-Over
added.description: Everyone is ecstatic when Bibi, Batgirl, and Robin capture Toyman and his Do-Over remote - except for Bibi, who failed to stick the landing on a big jump. Unwilling to accept her failure, Bibi uses Toyman's Do-Over remote until she perfects her jump!

added.title: Sidekicked to the Curb
added.description: When Bam is sent to take on Prank, Redbird is forced to hang back because The Joker's van is too dangerous! When Bam discovers that Redbird secretly tagged along, he's upset… until Redbird bails him out of a tight spot.

added.title: They Sent Us a Pie/Dust in the Wind
added.description: A giant pie is sent to Pretty Big City to stop an asteroid… but the Mechas and friends have eaten the whole thing!/The Singing Stone Heads are ready to perform at the Museum, but when they open their mouths, they sneeze instead of sing!

added.title: Pull Together/Lift Up and Lift Off
added.description: Ranger Nat is stuck at the bottom of the crevice, but the problem grows when Mecha Abby also gets stuck./Zee is ready to launch his rocket into space, but when the launchpad breaks, the rocket is launched into the farm instead.

added.title: Get in Gear/Free-Wheelin' Ferris Wheel
added.description: Panic erupts in Pretty Big City when the big clock breaks and no one is able to tell what time it is./Zee is showing off his inventions at his rocket-powered show, including his latest creation, a rocket powered Ferris wheel.

added.title: Thomas' Promise
added.description: When Thomas and Diesel both want to deliver the same load to Whiff's Recycling Plant, Thomas suggests they each take half of the load, but Diesel turns it into a race.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Thomas Blasts Off
added.description: It's rocket launch day and all the trains get to help deliver the big rocket parts, but when Thomas is assigned a tiny part, he puts it off to help the others with their more exciting parts, not realizing that his "small" task was just as important.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: License to Deliver
added.description: When Percy has to deliver a new light bulb to the lighthouse at night, Thomas suggests playing secret agents along the way to help Percy forget about his fear of the dark.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Rules of the Game
added.description: When Thomas builds an obstacle course for his friends, he gets upset when they won't play with it HIS way.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: A Quiet Delivery
added.description: Thomas volunteers to get a sleeping Annie and Clarabel across Sodor without waking them up, only to discover that it's going to be harder than he imagined.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Planets
added.description: Three, two, one, Blast Off! The BlippiMobile becomes a spacecraft on this mission to find out which planets are in the solar system! Merry the Meteor is the perfect host as Blippi is escorted through space and receives a guided tour of all the planets and their positions from the sun.

added.title: Fruit & Vegetables
added.description: On the hunt to discover the difference between fruits and vegetables, Blippi finds himself as a contestant in a community garden game show! Game show host Slim Cucumber quizzes Blippi on his knowledge of fruits and vegetables. Will Blippi know the answers?

added.title: Mountain
added.description: Blippi and TABBS head off on an icy adventure and fly up the side of Mt. Everest, the world's tallest mountain! They are joined by Betty the Yeti who is climbing to the top of the mountain in search of the ultimate snack - fresh snow!

added.title: Do the Skeleton Dance - Halloween Special
added.description: Lellobee City Farm learns to do the groovy Skeleton Dance for Halloween.

added.title: Wheels on the Bus
added.description: Ella and Mummy take the big red bus to Lellobee farm, where she meets Mia and the rest of the team!

added.title: Bedtime Song
added.description: Ella is getting ready for bed for a sleepover at Mei's house

removed.title: We are going on a egg hunt
removed.description: Ella, Rishi and Izzy are doing an egg hunt on the farm! Ella and Rishi both manage to find several but Izzy is not having much luck. Eventually she finds some eggs in the barn but much to the children's surprise and delight, when one of the eggs cracks open, a sweet little tortoise peeps out!

removed.title: Cousin Billy
removed.description: When Daffy's cool cousin Billy hires The Looney Builders to build her an art studio, Daffy tries to show off to prove how cool he is.

removed.title: Cheddar Days
removed.description: The Mouse Sisters hire The Looney Builders to build a cheese café featuring a mural by Sylvester who is having a bad day.

removed.title: Easter Bunny Hop
removed.description: Bunny Bun-Buns is going to do some baking but he needs some help collecting the ingredients. He hops around the farm with Ella and Rishi to collect some milk from Carlos, some eggs from Mama Duck and a carrot from the vegetable patch. Now they can bake his favourite thing - a carrot cake!

removed.title: Por unos Duncans mas
removed.description: Mientras trataba de fotocopiar su trasero en la nueva y elegante fotocopiadora del Chef, Duncan accidentalmente hace otro Duncan completo. iExcelente! Este otro Duncan puede hacer todas las cosas de la escuela mientras el verdadero Duncan se enfría. Pero las cosas van mal cuando el otro Duncan decide copiarse a sí mismo para poder relajarse también.

removed.title: Suenos Problematicos
removed.description: Izzy olvida el final de su sueño más asombroso de todos los tiempos, por lo que los niños viajan a su mente para descubrir qué sucedió.

removed.title: Las Dos Espadas
removed.description: Para escapar de la prisión del Hechicero Calavera, los Ninjas debe convencer a los Munces y a Geckles de que dejen de discutir y trabajen juntos.

removed.title: Ben sin fondo
removed.description: Los Tennyson se topan con un "pozo sin fondo": un pozo formado naturalmente, que carece de fondo. Ben se debate internamente si debe entrar o no, ihasta que llega Kevin 11 y empieza a incitarlo a hacer una carrera hacia abajo!

removed.title: La Reina de los Munces
removed.description: Jay, Nya y Lloyd son guiados entre las minas de Shintaro por Murt, quien los lleva de vuelta a la Cueva de los Munces. A la Reina Munce le gusta Jay.

removed.title: Somos Juguetes
removed.description: Cuando el Chef trae algunos juguetes viejos de su infancia, él, Duncan y Gwen, cada uno es absorbido mágicamente por uno de los juguetes y necesitan encontrar una manera de volver a sus propios cuerpos.

removed.title: Juicio de Mino
removed.description: Un grupo de Geckles creen que Kai y Zane están aliados con el Hechicero Calavera y los llevan con su líder, quien los somete a un juicio por Mino…

removed.title: En la Oscuridad
removed.description: La princesa Vania revela una entrada secreta que conduce a una mina subterránea bajo Shintaro donde se guardan los oscuros secretos de la ciudad.

removed.title: Quiero Ser Payaso
removed.description: Después de probarse la nariz de un payaso, Owen se entera de que así es como se hacen los payasos y está atrapado como un payaso hasta que puede engañar a otra persona para que le pida probarse la nariz.

removed.title: Dales aire y dejalos salir
removed.description: En la granja eólica de Mojave, Gwen y Max intentan enderezar las locas ideas de Ben sobre como funciona el viento. Pero cuando encuentran a los Climáticos usando las imponentes turbinas para sus viles objetivos, ¿podrá Ben aceptar los hechos a tiempo para derrotarlos?

removed.title: Aguafiestas
removed.description: Ben ignora completamente a Gwen cuando van a un centro de diversión familiar. Mientras tanto, Frightwig empuja a Zombozo a una vida de crímenes luego de que este termina convertido en un payaso para fiestas. iAhora, Zombozo y Ben deben aprender que no deberías ignorar a tus amigos!

removed.title: El Peor Rescate de la Historia
removed.description: Los Ninjas intentan rescatar a Cole, pero las discusiones entre prisioneros alertan al Hechicero Calavera, y hace prisioneros a los otros Ninjas.

removed.title: Historias del Omnitrix
removed.description: El Equipo Tennyson comparte historias de fogón en un episodio estilo antología, que enfrenta a Ben contra Kevin 11, su archirrival, y le enseña el poder de la imaginación a nuestro héroe.

removed.title: Grody al Maximo
removed.description: Cody recibe una camiseta nueva y genial. Es TAN genial que los niños ni siquiera lo reconocen, así que Cody aprovecha la oportunidad de dejar atrás su antigua vida y volverse popular.

removed.title: Game Over
